SUMMARY:Winter Improv Student Showcase
DESCRIPTION:Come see the improv stars of the future debut the skills they’ve learned in Unexpected Productions’ Improv School.\n\n\n\nJoin us tonight at Unexpected Productions’ Market Theater for the Winter Student Showcase! \nWatch as our talented students—ranging from beginner to advanced levels—take the stage to craft spontaneous\, engaging\, and often hilarious improv scenes right before your eyes. Our 300\, 400\, and 500-level students will showcase their newly honed skills\, giving you an exclusive preview of the next generation of improv stars. \nYou’ll experience a variety of performance styles inspired by UP’s mainstage shows\, making for an unpredictable and highly entertaining night. Stick around after the show to meet the performers—you’ll be able to say\, “I saw them before they were famous!” \n6:00pm: Chad Sunday 300\, Bestock 400\, Tim 400\, Tony 500\n8:00pm: Chad Monday 300\, Chazz 400\, Laurel 400\, Liz 500 \nDon’t miss this chance to support our rising improv stars and enjoy an evening of laughter and surprises. See you there!
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/winter-improv-student-showcase/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike Place Market\, Seattle\, WA\, 98101\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Student-Showcase-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
